.TH CMT_LOCAL 3 "CMT" "CMT_LOCAL" "Thread-Local Variables"

.SH NAME
CMT_LOCAL \- Marks global or static variables as thread-local

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #define INCL__LOCAL
.br
.B #include <CMT/CMT.H>

.SH FILES
CMT/KEYWORDS/LOCAL.H

.SH DESCRIPTION
Defines a macro to make a global or static variable thread-local, ensuring each thread has its own independent instance.

.TP
.B LOCAL, local
Marks a variable as thread-local.

.SH USAGE
.nf
// Global variable
local int g_variable = 0;

// Static variable inside a function
void test(void) {
    static local int variable = 0;
}
.fi

.SH NOTES
- Must only be used with global or static variables.
- Prevents unintended data sharing and race conditions between threads.
- Use 'local' in extern declarations for thread-local globals:
.nf
extern local int g_variable;
.fi

